  "prompt": "Is it allowed to watch ISRO satellite launch from safe distance at Sriharikota?",
  "response": "Yes, it is generally allowed to watch ISRO satellite launches from a designated viewing gallery at Satish Dhawan Space Centre (SDSC) in Sriharikota, but there are some important points to consider:\n\n*   **Availability:** Access to the viewing gallery is not guaranteed for every launch. It depends on factors like security concerns, the type of mission, and the capacity of the viewing gallery.\n*   **Registration:** To watch the launch from the viewing gallery, you typically need to register in advance on the ISRO website or a designated platform. Registration usually opens a few days before the launch and is often on a first-come, first-served basis due to limited capacity.\n*   **Launch Schedules:** Keep an eye on the ISRO website (www.isro.gov.in) for launch schedules and any announcements regarding viewing opportunities.\n*   **COVID-19:** Check for updated travel guidelines and COVID-19 restrictions before planning your visit.\n*   **Safety:** Follow all instructions and guidelines provided by ISRO and security personnel at the launch site.\n*   **Alternative Viewing Options:** If you cannot get access to the viewing gallery, you can still watch the launch live on ISRO's website, YouTube channel, or other official broadcast channels.\n*   **Distance:** Regardless of whether you have viewing gallery access, always maintain a safe distance from restricted areas and launch facilities.\n\nTo summarize, it's possible to watch ISRO launches from Sriharikota, but it requires advance planning, registration (if viewing gallery access is desired), and adherence to all safety guidelines. Check the ISRO website for the latest information regarding viewing opportunities for specific launches.",
